column5: I was sent this series of pictures via email a while ago. This took place in northern Ontario. Two Conservation Officers rescued this moose from a lumber mill settling pond. I finally got around to putting the pictures into a slide show. Hats off to those guys. http://s588.photobucket.com/user/hammercarp/slideshow/Moose%20Rescue .
Sorry Hammer, nothing came up but a basic blank page on Photobucket?
Link works fine.  That 'settling' slop looks gnarly!  Cool pics
Glad they got him out !!! Big moose that's for sure!!
Great job getting her out!!!!,amazing how relaxed she looked as they helped her get to her feet and balanced!.
That's awesome and not surprising for a mnr officer well at least all the ones I know. Thanks for taking the time to post the pictures.
Always good to see folks helping animals in distress.
Thats great! So glad they rescued that moose and even happier you had the pics to share!  Thanks
X2  That's wonderful to see!  Hope she is doing well.....

she is a he guys,  by photo's you can see the start of yearly antler growth in behind the eyes on a few shots. I'd guess this might have been spring time from the growth and that is a pretty tall body. That animal would have much greater mass in the fall  Good job by that crew
Well he's back to himself then lol.  .Great job.
